cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.CY 

The paper discusses strategies for analyzing multilingual event-centric information, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning and deep learning methods, which fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DL (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper touches on issues related to cybersecurity and privacy, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
